Today I headed over to the U.K. lIl be showing at BEYOND THE STREETS London starting Feb 17th. It'll mark the first time @beyondthenstreetsart goes international, taking over all 70,000 sq. ft. of the world-renowned Saatchi Gallery, with 100+ artists being showcased and plenty of stories being told throughout the gallery. As BTS likes to say, we'll be celebrating the rule-breakers and mark-makers from the world of graffiti, street art, punk rock and hip-hop, and all the moments that immortalized these subcultures in American and British history. If you find yourself in London come to @saatchi_gallery and see for yourself. Works will be on display from Feb. 17 - May 9, 2023. Thank you @rogergastman 
#BeyondTheStreets 
# London 
#SaatchiGallery

#thisislosangeles

Happy 45th Birthday to my Homie @murs316 . It’s cool when you get to make some art with people it’s even cooler when you become friends with some of those people. For those that don’t know , I shot the cover of “Fornever” Murs & @9thwonder and we @sastudiosglobal did the album layout, directed “The Problem Is” video, shot the Cover of “Have a Nice Life” and the latest cover “Take it Easy My Brother Murs” throughout the years we’ve worked on other projects as well but aside from that we are Friends . Nothing but love for you homie , thank you for the friendship, the work we did and all you did for L.A. and Hip Hop.

We are honored to bring to you @estevanoriol latest creation, "Momento Mori," is a captivating hand-pulled screen print, measuring 20x28 inches. This limited edition art piece, printed on 300gsm White Vellum Coventry Rag. All order will be shipped flat and insured. Use code: ALLSKULLS at checkout for free shipping. This edition is an exceptional fusion of Oriol's distinctive urban aesthetic and a profound exploration of life's transience. Each color way of this masterpiece is limited to only five prints per color way , making "Momento Mori" a truly exclusive and highly coveted addition to any art collection. 🔒💀

Spent my Thanksgiving morning volunteering at Project Angel Food, where we served 2,500 meals to critically ill Angelenos who often spend the holiday alone. Each client received two meals, ensuring they have food to share with caregivers or neighbors. Proud to be part of an organization that provides medically tailored meals to 2,500 people daily. With 1.6 million meals served this year, Project Angel Food continues to make a difference. Since 1989, they’ve delivered over 17 million meals. Support their cause at 
Angelfood.org/thanksgiving23.

Hip hop til infinity 

Opening today at the old amoeba store on sunset Blvd and cahuenga Blvd . If you like Hip hop or just music period this is a great exhibit for you to see. I got a room in the back corner , brought in some memorabilia. I got 4 walls of of my stuff . 1 Nipsey Hussle, 2. Hip hop, 3. Lowriding , 4. Prison and gangster art, all parts of L.A. hip hop. Also the have my photos projected from floor to ceiling in that room and a couple others . Wednesday , Thursday 12pm -8pm Friday-Sunday 12pm - 11:30pm . 
@hiphop.tilinfinity @hiphop50 by @massappeal 
They got a lot of my merch in there along with some other cool stuff.
